
[1]visage

   VIS'AGE, n. s as z. [L. visus, video.]

   The face; the countenance or look of a person, or of other animal;
   chiefly applied to human beings; as a wolfish visage.

   Love and beauty still that visage grace.

   His visage was so marred, more than any man. Is. 52.
